back/.zed
```json back/.zed/settings.json
{
  "dev_container": {
    "enabled": true,
    "compose_file": ["docker-compose.yml", ".devcontainer/docker-compose.yml"],
    "service": "api"
  },
  "language_servers": {
    "python": {
      "enabled": true,
      "command": ["pylsp"],
      "environment": {
        "PYTHONPATH": "/app"
      }
    }
  },
  "formatter": {
    "python": {
      "command": "black",
      "arguments": ["--quiet", "-"]
    }
  }
}
```



I have an error telling " Invalid type: map, expected a sequence"
The error occurs because the `compose_file` value in `dev_container` should be a string, not an array. Here's the corrected version:

```json
{
  "dev_container": {
    "enabled": true,
    "compose_file": "docker-compose.yml",
    "service": "api"
  },
  "language_servers": {
    "python": {
      "enabled": true,
      "command": ["pylsp"],
      "environment": {
        "PYTHONPATH": "/app"
      }
    }
  },
  "formatter": {
    "python": {
      "command": "black",
      "arguments": ["--quiet", "-"]
    }
  }
}
```

If you need to specify multiple compose files, you should use a string with paths separated by a colon `:`, like this:

```json
"compose_file": "docker-compose.yml:.devcontainer/docker-compose.yml"
```

This should resolve the "Invalid type" error you're seeing.
